Again, another try to get as many 10 minute exposures together, which was in this case not as bad since it is a pure HOO image, so just 2 channels. And ... I can image this nebula all through the night (Cindy, I hear you ... ðŸ˜Š), no trees in the way, so just letting it run overnight is nice, also knowing that the weather will hold up with 0% chance of rain. The dates of the data captured reflect the last night of multiple ones per channel.
I always liked this PN, with its nice blue originator star in the middle. This almost wraps up my excursion with the achromat (one more to go), gave me a lot of pleasure and nice results.
Info: Constellation: Lynx; Mag: 14; Distance: 1600 LJs; 16.8-mag central star is a very blue white dwarf.
title: Jones-Emberson 1; PK164+31.1 - Headphone Nebula
